<all><div style="display: none;" class="doc-user-reviews-page num-pagination-page" data-pageid="0"><div class="doc-review"><span class="doc-review-author"><strong>Peter</strong></span><span class="doc-review-date"> - June 27, 2012</span> - Version 2.5.0<span><a href="/store/apps/details?id=com.httechltd.beatbuddy&amp;reviewId=13311586027752345145"><div class="goog-inline-block review-permalink" title="Link to this review"></div></a></span><div class="doc-review-ratings-line"><div class="ratings goog-inline-block" title="Rating: 2.0 stars (Below average)"><div class="goog-inline-block star SPRITE_star_on_dark"></div><div class="goog-inline-block star SPRITE_star_on_dark"></div><div class="goog-inline-block star SPRITE_star_off_dark"></div><div class="goog-inline-block star SPRITE_star_off_dark"></div><div class="goog-inline-block star SPRITE_star_off_dark"></div></div><h4 class="review-title">No search tool?</h4></div><p class="review-text">Latest version looks slicker but I just don't like having to navigate the hierarchies and remember where each entry is.  My brain is confused seeing a general heading like "Crime" at the same level in the menu structure as the very specific "Licensing Act 2003", and "People" (don't all offences involve people somehow?).  The app forces you to understand the logic of the designer, rather than the designer making the categories intuitive and simple.  IMHO it really needs a rethink and a SEARCH tool like "Quick Reference for UK Police".  On the plus side there's plenty of detailed content (full legal wording) but sometimes a quick summary would be nicer for those of us who don't speak "Legal" :)</p><div class="review-footer goog-inline-block"><div class="doc-review-label">&#160;</div><div class="per-review-controls goog-inline-block"></div></div></div> <div class="doc-review"><span class="doc-review-author"><strong>Abul</strong></span><span class="doc-review-date"> - June 15, 2012</span> - Samsung Galaxy S2 with version 2.5.0<span><a